So that's actually critical.

00:09:41.470 --> 00:09:43.910
I wonder if we could maybe
just back up a second

00:09:43.910 --> 00:09:47.130
and just talk a little bit
about the theoretical framework

00:09:47.130 --> 00:09:48.660
for understanding mate choice.

00:09:48.660 --> 00:09:51.220
So it basically stems from

00:09:51.220 --> 00:09:53.510
Darwin's theory of sexual selection,

00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:55.570
and most people, when they
think about evolution,

00:09:55.570 --> 00:09:59.410
they think about, the cliche
is like survival of the fittest

00:09:59.410 --> 00:10:02.180
or nature, red in tooth and claw.

00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:05.120
And Darwin noticed that
there were phenomena

00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:06.450
that couldn't be explained

00:10:06.450 --> 00:10:09.020
by this so-called survival selection,

00:10:09.020 --> 00:10:11.930
things like the brilliant
plumage of peacocks,

00:10:11.930 --> 00:10:15.510
sex differences, like in,
you know, stags, for example,

00:10:15.510 --> 00:10:17.290
have these massive antlers

00:10:17.290 --> 00:10:19.513
and the females of the species do not.

00:10:20.553 --> 00:10:23.130
And so he came up with the
theory of sexual selection,

00:10:23.130 --> 00:10:25.860
which deals not with the
evolution of characteristics

00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:27.980
due to their survival advantage,

00:10:27.980 --> 00:10:30.420
but rather due to their mating advantage.

00:10:30.420 --> 00:10:33.350
And he identified two causal processes

00:10:33.350 --> 00:10:35.980
by which mating advantage could occur.

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:40.360
One is intrasexual competition
with the stereotyping,

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:43.330
two stags locking horns in combat

00:10:43.330 --> 00:10:46.790
with the victor gaining
sexual access to the female,

00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:49.150
loser ambling off with a broken antler

00:10:49.150 --> 00:10:51.220
and dejected in low self-esteem

00:10:51.220 --> 00:10:53.273
and needing psychotherapy perhaps,

00:10:54.584 --> 00:10:57.803
or mate value improvement therapy.

00:10:59.336 --> 00:11:00.770
And the logic was whatever qualities

00:11:00.770 --> 00:11:03.140
led to success in these same-sex battles,

00:11:03.140 --> 00:11:05.860
those qualities get passed
on in greater numbers.

00:11:05.860 --> 00:11:07.030
And so you see evolution,

00:11:07.030 --> 00:11:10.440
which is change over time
and increase in frequency

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:13.990
of the characteristics
associated with winning these,

00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:16.460
what Darwin called contest competition.

00:11:16.460 --> 00:11:19.000
And we know that the logic
of that is more general now

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.080
and involves things like in our species

00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:24.310
competing for position
in status hierarchies.

00:11:24.310 --> 00:11:27.450
So anyway, so intrasexual
competition is one,

00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:31.000
but the second most
relevant to your question

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:34.020
about mate choice is
preferential mate choice,

00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:36.420
that was the second causal pathway.

00:11:36.420 --> 00:11:38.810
And the logic there is that

00:11:38.810 --> 00:11:41.330
if members of one sex
agree with one another,

00:11:41.330 --> 00:11:43.160
if there's some consensus

00:11:43.160 --> 00:11:45.480
about the qualities that are desired,

00:11:45.480 --> 00:11:47.080
then those of the opposite sex

00:11:47.080 --> 00:11:48.880
who possess the desired qualities

00:11:48.880 --> 00:11:51.070
or embody those desired qualities,

00:11:51.070 --> 00:11:52.830
they have a mating advantage.

00:11:52.830 --> 00:11:55.400
They get chosen, they get preferred.

00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:57.910
Those lacking desired
qualities get banished,

00:11:57.910 --> 00:11:58.970
shunned, ignored,

00:11:58.970 --> 00:12:02.450
or in the modern
