00:25:13.860 --> 00:25:16.630
with women preferring somewhat older men,

00:25:16.630 --> 00:25:19.240
and men preferring somewhat younger women.

00:25:19.240 --> 00:25:20.730
Is there a consistent age gap

00:25:22.800 --> 00:25:24.480
to relate to that statement?

00:25:24.480 --> 00:25:25.810
- Yes, there is.

00:25:25.810 --> 00:25:30.810
So the age gap though depends
on the age of the man.

00:25:31.412 --> 00:25:34.790
So, we can document this,

00:25:34.790 --> 00:25:35.740
so in my studies,

00:25:35.740 --> 00:25:38.380
what we found is that men preferred women

00:25:38.380 --> 00:25:40.690
who were about three to four years

00:25:40.690 --> 00:25:43.360
younger than they were on average.

00:25:43.360 --> 00:25:44.930
And I'll qualify this in a second.

00:25:44.930 --> 00:25:46.711
Women preferred guys who were about

00:25:46.711 --> 00:25:49.370
three and a half to four
and a half years older

00:25:49.370 --> 00:25:50.203
than they were.

00:25:50.203 --> 00:25:51.130
So there was a sex difference

00:25:51.130 --> 00:25:52.883
going in the opposite direction.

00:25:53.950 --> 00:25:55.830
But as men get older,

00:25:55.830 --> 00:25:56.880
they prefer women who are

00:25:56.880 --> 00:25:59.430
increasingly younger than they are.

00:25:59.430 --> 00:26:01.770
So one way to gauge this,

00:26:01.770 --> 00:26:05.830
so there are actual marriage statistics,

00:26:05.830 --> 00:26:08.900
and then there are expressed preferences,

00:26:08.900 --> 00:26:11.040
and both sexes kind of converge.

00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:15.440
So if you look at, you
know, first marriage,

00:26:15.440 --> 00:26:17.040
second marriage, third marriage,

00:26:17.040 --> 00:26:19.220
if people get divorced and remarried.

00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:21.970
Average age gap is, in America anyway,

00:26:21.970 --> 00:26:23.650
is three years at first marriage

00:26:23.650 --> 00:26:25.113
with the guys being older,

00:26:26.530 --> 00:26:28.140
five years at second marriage,

00:26:28.140 --> 00:26:30.093
and eight years at third marriage.

00:26:31.610 --> 00:26:34.050
So that is, as men are getting older

00:26:34.050 --> 00:26:35.700
and getting divorced and remarried,

00:26:35.700 --> 00:26:36.640
they are marrying women

00:26:36.640 --> 00:26:39.150
who are increasingly
younger than they are.

00:26:39.150 --> 00:26:40.940
In terms of preferences,

00:26:40.940 --> 00:26:43.030
it's also expressed in preferences.

00:26:43.030 --> 00:26:46.110
So it doesn't go down, so like a,

00:26:46.110 --> 00:26:49.410
say a 25-year-old man would say,

00:26:49.410 --> 00:26:53.250
prefer a woman who's
20 or in her early 20s,

00:26:53.250 --> 00:26:55.480
35-year-old man might prefer a woman

00:26:55.480 --> 00:26:58.993
who's in her late 20s or early 30s.

00:27:00.579 --> 00:27:02.270
A 50-year-old man might prefer a woman

00:27:02.270 --> 00:27:04.953
who is say, 35 to 38.

00:27:05.908 --> 00:27:09.090
So the preferences do go up,

00:27:09.090 --> 00:27:11.940
but the gap gets increasingly larger.

00:27:11.940 --> 00:27:15.440
And the reason that you
don't see things like,

00:27:15.440 --> 00:27:17.170
why aren't men preferring women?

00:27:17.170 --> 00:27:20.953
So peak fertility in humans
is around age 24, 25.

00:27:22.317 --> 00:27:23.310
And so you say, well,

00:27:23.310 --> 00:27:26.150
why aren't the 60-year-old men

00:27:26.150 --> 00:27:28.540
