00:29:39.120 --> 00:29:40.470
it basically stayed the same,

00:29:40.470 --> 00:29:42.830
it was in the early twenties or so.

00:29:42.830 --> 00:29:44.273
- He values consistency.

00:29:45.120 --> 00:29:46.033
- Consistency.

00:29:47.040 --> 00:29:51.360
But, so anyway, the data converge on that.

00:29:51.360 --> 00:29:54.260
So these are universal sex differences

00:29:54.260 --> 00:29:57.430
in long-term mate selection.

00:29:57.430 --> 00:29:59.497
So now when we shift to,

00:29:59.497 --> 00:30:02.540
and I should mention cultural variability,

00:30:02.540 --> 00:30:03.620
because that's a critical thing,

00:30:03.620 --> 00:30:06.660
because there is in my 37 culture study,

00:30:06.660 --> 00:30:10.110
what I found was the
preference for virginity,

00:30:10.110 --> 00:30:13.390
that is no prior sexual experience,

00:30:13.390 --> 00:30:18.350
that was the most variable
desire across cultures.

00:30:18.350 --> 00:30:23.350
So you had cultures, like at
the time of the study, China,

00:30:24.330 --> 00:30:28.990
it was basically indispensable
that a partner be a virgin.

00:30:28.990 --> 00:30:30.470
And then at the other end,

00:30:30.470 --> 00:30:34.220
you have Sweden where
Swedes typically place

00:30:34.220 --> 00:30:35.337
close to zero value on it,

00:30:35.337 --> 00:30:37.690
and some even find it undesirable.

00:30:37.690 --> 00:30:40.310
Like, you're weird if you're a virgin.

00:30:40.310 --> 00:30:42.450
And so you have this whole spectrum.

00:30:42.450 --> 00:30:45.763
- This is virginity in the
female, or is this also,

00:30:46.810 --> 00:30:48.310
in China was it preference

00:30:48.310 --> 00:30:50.070
that the male and the female be virgins?

00:30:50.070 --> 00:30:51.580
It's a mutual mate a selection?

00:30:51.580 --> 00:30:53.680
- Yeah, it was a
preference for both sexes.

00:30:53.680 --> 00:30:54.900
- Interesting.

00:30:54.900 --> 00:30:56.550
- But it's a good question,

00:30:56.550 --> 00:30:58.740
because where there was a sex difference,

00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:00.330
it was always in the direction

00:31:00.330 --> 00:31:03.750
of males preferring
virginity more than females,

00:31:03.750 --> 00:31:05.610
and we've gone back to China.

00:31:05.610 --> 00:31:09.150
So I still do research in
China among other places.

00:31:09.150 --> 00:31:13.480
And we've gone back and retested
modern urban populations,

00:31:13.480 --> 00:31:17.820
and the importance of virginity
has gone down in China,

00:31:17.820 --> 00:31:19.670
especially in the urban areas,

00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:22.650
and the sex difference
that didn't exist before,

00:31:22.650 --> 00:31:26.010
has now emerged, where males
value it more than females.

00:31:26.010 --> 00:31:30.160
And I think part of it
was in previous times,

00:31:30.160 --> 00:31:33.450
you hit ceiling effects, you
know, where both sexes say,

00:31:33.450 --> 00:31:36.733
yeah, it's absolutely
important to be a Virgin.

00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:42.310
So, there's cultural variation
and cultural change over time

00:31:42.310 --> 00:31:44.013
in some of these qualities.

00:31:45.850 --> 00:31:48.190
But the sex differences that I described

00:31:48.190 --> 00:31:50.480
have remained invariant over the years.

00:31:50.480 --> 00:31:53.500
So since my 37 culture study,

00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:55.040
this has been replicated in,

00:31:55.040 --> 00:31:57.783
at least a couple of
dozen different cultures,

00:31:58.783 --> 00:32:01.030
and we've gone back to
some of the cultures.

00:32:01.030 --> 00:32:06.030
So I mentioned, we've gone back
to China, Brazil, and India,

00:32:06.460 --> 00:32:08.560
to look at cultural changes over time,

00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:11.720
and there have been,
you know, in some cases,

00:32:11.720 --> 00:32:14.070
dramatic cultural changes over time.

00:32:14.070 --> 00:32:17.140
But the sex differences that
I described are invariant.

00:32:17.140 --> 00:32:19.520
They haven't changed a bit.

00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:20.940
- I'd be remiss if I didn't ask

00:32:20.940 --> 00:32:23.620
about truth telling and deception,

00:32:23.620 --> 00:32:26.350
because some of the measures
that you're describing,

00:32:26.350 --> 00:32:31.350
age, for instance, one can
potentially lie about, right?

00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:32.560
I'm guessing that there are people

00:32:32.560 --> 00:32:35.233
who do that on online
profiles and whatnot.

00:32:36.360 --> 00:32:37.840
From what I understand,

00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:41.040
people also lie about
height and other features

00:32:41.040 --> 00:32:43.120
on online profiles,

00:32:43.120 --> 00:32:45.750
but some of them are much
harder to hide, right?

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:49.210
Eventually the truth comes out about some,

00:32:49.210 --> 00:32:50.670
if not all of these things.

00:32:50.670 --> 00:32:53.300
So, if you would,

00:32:53.300 --> 00:32:57.410
could you tell us about how men and women

00:32:57.410 --> 00:32:59.930
leverage deception versus truth telling

00:32:59.930 --> 00:33:01.310
and communicating some of the things

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:03.960
around mate choice selection?

00:33:03.960 --> 00:33:04.793
- Yeah, well,

00:33:04.793 --> 00:33:09.060
so basically both men
and women do deceive,

00:33:09.060 --> 00:33:13.840
so we have the modern cultural
invention of online dating,

00:33:13.840 --> 00:33:15.130
which, you know,

00:33:15.130 --> 00:33:18.020
was little-used 10 years ago,

00:33:18.020 --> 00:33:20.513
and virtually absent 20 years ago.

00:33:21.610 --> 00:33:25.210
And people do lie, but they
lie in predictable ways.

00:33:25.210 --> 00:33:28.710
They lie in ways that attempt to embody

00:33:28.710 --> 00:33:30.700
the mate preferences of the person

00:33:30.700 --> 00:33:32.090
they're trying to attract.

00:33:32.090 --> 00:33:34.050
And so men do lie.

00:33:34.050 --> 00:33:37.610
They deceive about their
income, their status.

00:33:37.610 --> 00:33:40.783
So they exaggerate their
income by about 20%.

00:33:43.410 --> 00:33:45.600
They tack on about two
inches to their height.

00:33:45.600 --> 00:33:48.163
So if they're five ten,
they round up to six feet.

00:33:49.500 --> 00:33:51.170
So they don't like, if they're five ten,

00:33:51.170 --> 00:33:53.150
they don't say that they're gigantic,

00:33:53.150 --> 00:33:55.150
but they kind of round it up

00:33:55.150 --> 00:33:57.373
in the more desirable direction.

00:33:58.430 --> 00:34:00.980
Women tend to deceive about weight.

00:34:00.980 --> 00:34:03.320
So they tend to shave about 15 pounds

00:34:03.320 --> 00:34:05.560
off of their reported weight,

00:34:05.560 --> 00:34:10.550
and both sexes post photos that
are not truly representative

00:34:10.550 --> 00:34:11.980
of what they actually look like.

00:34:11.980 --> 00:34:15.430
So they might post photos
of themselves when they were

00:34:15.430 --> 00:34:18.493
younger, or they're even advice,

00:34:20.850 --> 00:34:25.710
tips on how to create the best
selfie, of the best angle,

00:34:25.710 --> 00:34:29.400
that will maximally, you know,
enhance what you look like.

00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:32.010
- Or just doctoring of
photos I'm guessing.

00:34:32.010 --> 00:34:34.460
- Oh yeah, Photoshopping, absolutely.

00:34:34.460 --> 00:34:39.390
And one of the things about
it now, you say, well,

00:34:39.390 --> 00:34:42.800
do people find out, of
course, people do find out.

00:34:42.800 --> 00:34:45.210
I'll just give you one story
about a colleague of mine,

00:34:45.210 --> 00:34:48.150
who is a male, who's
doing internet dating.

00:34:48.150 --> 00:34:53.020
And he picked only women
who self-described as sevens

00:34:53.020 --> 00:34:54.850
on the one to seven on attractiveness.

00:34:54.850 --> 00:34:58.180
So the most attractive, as self-reported,

00:34:58.180 --> 00:35:00.600
and se he went out with this one woman,

00:35:00.600 --> 00:35:03.510
and she was missing her front teeth.

00:35:03.510 --> 00:35:06.500
And he said, well, call me picky,

00:35:06.500 --> 00:35:08.510
but missing her front teeth.

00:35:08.510 --> 00:35:11.050
And she thinks she's like
the top of attractiveness,

00:35:11.050 --> 00:35:13.830
he was a little disappointed about that.

00:35:13.830 --> 00:35:15.860
And women of course are disappointed,

00:35:15.860 --> 00:35:19.320
they meet a guy who they
think is this physically fit,

00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:21.050
you know, athletic guy,

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:25.340
and he comes up he's, you know,
300 pounds and overweight.

00:35:25.340 --> 00:35:27.819
So people do find out.

00:35:27.819 --> 00:35:31.310
And there are some
internet dating sites have

00:35:32.620 --> 00:35:36.660
kind of a vetting of the
accuracy of something.

00:35:36.660 --> 00:35:39.100
So some things you can look
up through public records,

00:35:39.100 --> 00:35:42.590
and does this guy have a
criminal record, for example,

00:35:42.590 --> 00:35:47.590
is he on a, you know, a
sexual offenders website?

00:35:49.846 --> 00:35:51.670
So there's some things you can verify.

00:35:51.670 --> 00:35:53.573
But what I tell people is,

00:35:54.640 --> 00:35:57.470
you really have to meet the
person and interact, you know,

00:35:57.470 --> 00:36:00.000
because in part because of the deception,

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:04.010
but also because what
happens with internet dating

00:36:04.010 --> 00:36:07.930
is that the photograph tends to overwhelm

00:36:07.930 --> 00:36:11.040
all the other cues and all the other cues

00:36:11.040 --> 00:36:12.610
are written statements.

00:36:12.610 --> 00:36:17.200
And we weren't really evolved
to process written statements,

00:36:17.200 --> 00:36:21.743
but we were evolved to
respond to physical cues, but,

00:36:23.540 --> 00:36:27.420
and men tend to attend to the visual cues

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:28.590
much more than women.

00:36:28.590 --> 00:36:30.490
So women in their mate selection,

00:36:30.490 --> 00:36:33.890
they have olfactory cues to
what does the guy sound like?

00:36:33.890 --> 00:36:35.283
His vocal qualities,

00:36:37.160 --> 00:36:39.980
that's auditory cues,

00:36:39.980 --> 00:36:42.330
but olfactory cues,
what does he smell like?

00:36:42.330 --> 00:36:47.080
And so women have a more acute
sense of smell than men do.

00:36:47.080 --> 00:36:49.690
And so if the guy doesn't smell right,

00:36:49.690 --> 00:36:52.970
even if he embodies all these
other qualities women want,

00:36:52.970 --> 00:36:54.093
that's a deal breaker.

00:36:55.460 --> 00:36:58.730
And so I encourage people just, you know,

00:36:58.730 --> 00:37:02.340
stop with a hundred texts
back and forth or messaging,

00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:05.380
and meet a person for a
cup of coffee and interact.

00:37:05.380 --> 00:37:06.670
And then you'll, you know,

00:37:06.670 --> 00:37:09.940
you'll get a more accurate
bead on the person.

00:37:09.940 --> 00:37:11.930
And then of course, some
qualities you can't assess

00:37:11.930 --> 00:37:16.170
even with a half-hour
interaction, you can tell a lot,

00:37:16.170 --> 00:37:19.090
but things like emotional stability,

00:37:19.090 --> 00:37:22.880
or things that have to
be assessed over time.

00:37:22.880 --> 00:37:26.600
And so one of the things
that I advise people to do,

00:37:26.600 --> 00:37:28.220
and I'm not in the advice-giving business,

00:37:28.220 --> 00:37:30.029
but people ask me all the time.

00:37:30.029 --> 00:37:32.630
If they find out what I
study, they say, well,

00:37:32.630 --> 00:37:35.240
I got this problem,
can you give me advice?

00:37:35.240 --> 00:37:36.510
But one of the things to assess,

00:37:36.510 --> 00:37:38.490
things like emotional stability,

00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:41.810
which is absolutely critical
in long-term mating,

00:37:41.810 --> 00:37:44.910
is to do something like
go on a trip together,

00:37:44.910 --> 00:37:47.430
take a vacation where you're

00:37:47.430 --> 00:37:51.250
even in an unfamiliar environment where

00:37:51.250 --> 00:37:54.039
you have to cope with things
that you're not familiar with.

00:37:54.039 --> 00:37:57.170
And as opposed to an environment

00:37:57.170 --> 00:37:58.820
where it's very predictable,

00:37:58.820 --> 00:38:01.290
and so you get a greater exposure,

00:38:01.290 --> 00:38:06.290
because one of the hallmarks
of emotional instability

00:38:07.450 --> 00:38:10.550
is how they respond to stress.

00:38:10.550 --> 00:38:14.870
So emotionally unstable people
tend to have a long latency

00:38:14.870 --> 00:38:18.500
to return to baseline
after a stressful event.

00:38:18.500 --> 00:38:20.460
And so this is the sort of information

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:23.720
you can't get on a coffee date,

00:38:23.720 --> 00:38:26.520
you can only get by
assessing it over time.

00:38:26.520 --> 00:38:28.530
- Somebody whose laboratory studies stress

00:38:28.530 --> 00:38:30.203
and tools to combat stress.

00:38:31.120 --> 00:38:33.010
That's great, it's yet
more incentive for people

00:38:33.010 --> 00:38:36.913
to develop self-regulatory
mechanisms for themselves.

00:38:37.840 --> 00:38:42.230
I'm guessing many of the
features of deception

00:38:42.230 --> 00:38:45.860
in this context were present
