01:38:16.130 --> 01:38:18.160
well she was with me once,

01:38:18.160 --> 01:38:21.283
maybe I can get her back with me again.

01:38:23.148 --> 01:38:26.513
So the psychology is very understandable,

01:38:27.680 --> 01:38:29.690
but it tends not to work because,

01:38:29.690 --> 01:38:30.770
and then the other thing we found,

01:38:30.770 --> 01:38:34.260
we did a study of 2,500
victims of stalking.

01:38:34.260 --> 01:38:36.780
This is with Josh Duntley,
a former student of mine,

01:38:36.780 --> 01:38:39.280
who's now a professor in
the criminology department.

01:38:39.280 --> 01:38:43.630
And what we found is there were large sex,

01:38:43.630 --> 01:38:45.940
large differences between the stalker

01:38:45.940 --> 01:38:47.610
and the victim of the stalker,

01:38:47.610 --> 01:38:50.430
where the stalker tends to be much lower

01:38:50.430 --> 01:38:52.960
in mate value than the victim.

01:38:52.960 --> 01:38:55.680
And so basically it's typically the woman

01:38:55.680 --> 01:39:00.150
who realizes she can do a lot
better on the mating market,

01:39:00.150 --> 01:39:03.440
and the guy realizes I
am never going to be able

01:39:03.440 --> 01:39:07.330
to replace her with a woman
of equivalent mate value.

01:39:07.330 --> 01:39:11.300
And so I'm going to use this
last ditch desperate measure

01:39:11.300 --> 01:39:14.313
to try to get her back,
and occasionally it works.

01:39:16.312 --> 01:39:20.303
- I'm thinking more about
this mate value thing,

01:39:21.860 --> 01:39:25.580
this number, this metric,
the eight, ten, six,

01:39:25.580 --> 01:39:27.250
whatever it is.

01:39:27.250 --> 01:39:29.760
And mate value discrepancy
playing such a strong role

01:39:29.760 --> 01:39:31.323
in all these dynamics.

01:39:32.500 --> 01:39:33.820
