somebody else of something

02:02:23.260 --> 02:02:24.810
that secretly they know isn't true,

02:02:24.810 --> 02:02:27.600
but that they deceive themselves.

02:02:27.600 --> 02:02:28.930
Could you embellish on that a little bit?

02:02:28.930 --> 02:02:31.220
- Well, this is actually, this hypothesis

02:02:32.066 --> 02:02:34.520
is the famous evolutionary
biologist, Robert Trivers,

02:02:34.520 --> 02:02:37.740
first advanced this
hypothesis in the preface,

02:02:37.740 --> 02:02:42.360
in 1976 to Dawkins'
book, The Selfish Gene.

02:02:42.360 --> 02:02:46.080
And he's subsequently
written more about it,

02:02:46.080 --> 02:02:49.920
both in scientific article
and in a more popular book.

02:02:49.920 --> 02:02:54.920
But the idea is, the core idea
is that successful deception

02:02:55.010 --> 02:02:57.800
is facilitated by self-deception.

02:02:57.800 --> 02:03:02.600
So if you really believe that in X,

02:03:02.600 --> 02:03:04.740
then you're going to be a
more successful salesman

02:03:04.740 --> 02:03:06.740
to convince other people of X.

02:03:06.740 --> 02:03:08.310
So if you believe you're,

02:03:08.310 --> 02:03:10.380
let's say a 10 in mate value,

02:03:10.380 --> 02:03:13.600
you truly believe it, even if you're not,

02:03:13.600 --> 02:03:15.780
I'm going to have a more successful time

02:03:15.780 --> 02:03:17.830
convincing you that I am as well.

02:03:17.830 --> 02:03:20.220
And so the hypothesis is basically

02:03:20.220 --> 02:03:24.470
that people self-deceive
in order to increase

02:03:24.470 --> 02:03:26.843
the effectiveness of actual deception.

02:03:29.590 --> 02:03:31.660
But I think that there are people who

02:03:33.970 --> 02:03:36.910
are so in one other
dimension I'll mention too,

02:03:36.910 --> 02:03:39.610
is that as that animals
often take each other

02:03:39.610 --> 02:03:41.790
at our own word for things.

02:03:41.790 --> 02:03:43.620
So if we're self-confident,

02:03:43.620 --> 02:03:46.100
